LEMMAS / THEOREMS PROVEN (sorry-free):

  Definitions:
    MChain.b_vec                  - single-conv b(k) vector (= BB_W with l=2)
    MChain.Delta_b                - LP closed-form Delta_b(k) (= Delta_BB l=2)
    MChain.n_pairs                - # pairs with i+j=k (= ell_int_arr)
    MChain.pair_set               - pair set {(i,j) : i+j=k} (= window_pair_set l=2)
    MChain.LB                     - M-chain lower bound (per-position)

  Helper theorems:
    MChain.icc_singleton          - Icc s (s+l-2) = {s} when l=2
    MChain.b_vec_eq               - b(k)_j = sum_i [i+j=k] * c_i
    MChain.pair_set_eq            - pair_set = window_pair_set k 2
    MChain.pair_set_eq_filter     - pair_set = filter (i+j=k)
    MChain.pair_set_card          - |pair_set| = n_pairs(k)
    MChain.linear_identity_left   - sum_p c(p.1)d(p.2) = sum_j d_j b(k)_j
    MChain.linear_identity_right  - sum_p d(p.1)c(p.2) = sum_j d_j b(k)_j
    MChain.conv_decomposition     - sum a_i a_j = sum c_i c_j + 2L + Q
    MChain.discrete_autoconv_eq_pair_sum - DA(a,k) = sum a_i a_j over pair_set

  Core mathematical lemmas (matching m_chain_proof.md):
    MChain.lemma_A   - Lemma A (convolution at breakpoint, integer c).
                       Re-exports convolution_at_grid_point from StepFunction.lean.
    MChain.lemma_B   - Lemma B (LP closed-form lower bound).
                       sum_j delta_j * b(k)_j >= -Delta_b(k) under |delta|<=1, sum=0.
                       Proof: invoke lp_closed_form_le on -delta with h=1.
    MChain.lemma_C   - Lemma C (quadratic bound).
                       |sum_{i+j=k} delta_i delta_j| <= n_pairs(k) under |delta|<=1.
                       Both lemma_C_abs (absolute-value) and lemma_C (lower-bound).
    MChain.lemma_D   - Lemma D (cell polytope subset P_d^c subset P_d).
                       delta_j >= -min(c_j,1), delta_j <= 1 ==> |delta_j| <= 1.

  Main theorems:
    MChain.core_lower_bound       - Integer-mass cell:
                                    sum a_i a_j >= sum c_i c_j - 2 Delta_b - n_pairs.
    MChain.main_per_position      - TV-style:
                                    LB(k) <= (1/(4n)/m^2) * sum a_i a_j.
    MChain.main_DA_form           - DA-style:
                                    LB(k) <= DA(a,k) / (4 n m^2).
    MChain.LB_step_at_c           - Pointwise at integer c (delta=0):
                                    LB(k) <= (step * step)(t_k).
    MChain.cell_prune_per_position - Cell-prune soundness:
                                    LB(k) > c_target  ==>  DA(a,k)/(4n m^2) > c_target.

  Sanity examples:
    n_pairs 1 1 = 2,  n_pairs 1 0 = 1,  n_pairs 1 2 = 1.

