═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

The file proves the full M-chain mathematical core. What remains for a
publication-grade Lean formalisation:

1. M-chain in CONTINUOUS form for arbitrary cell variable a:
   Prove that for real a (not integer c), there exists a step function
   step_function_real n m a with the same convolution-at-breakpoint
   property; then (step_function_real * step_function_real)(t_k) >= LB(k)
   follows from MChain.main_per_position.

   Currently: only step_function n m c (integer-c) is proven via
   convolution_at_grid_point. The bridge to real a is straightforward
   but requires re-running the measure-theoretic lemmas in
   StepFunction.lean for real heights.  Out of scope here.

2. Cascade integration: chaining MChain.cell_prune_per_position into the
   CascadePruned inductive predicate from Sidon.Defs. This is a
   straightforward case-split on direct vs. refine - a one-page wrap
   in a separate file.

3. Step-vs-continuous gap (m_chain_proof.md sec.7a): proving that step
   pruning implies continuous f pruning. This is the open math problem
   discussed in the proof document, not a Lean formalisation gap.

